            "description": "In laterite soils and soils of sloppy land in heavy rainfall areas (west coast), the fertilizer should be applied in circular trenches of 25 cm width and 15 cm depth prepared at a distance of 0.5m- 0.7m, 1m - 1.5m away from the trunk during the first, second, third and fourth year onwards of planting respectively. The trenches should be closed immediately after the fertilizer application. Preferably apply mulch of green leaves for enhancing the fertilizer- use efficiency."
